President Trump addressed the American Farm Bureau at the Gaylord Opryland Resort and Convention Center in Nashville, Tennessee. He thanked Secretary of Agriculture Sonny Perdue and expressed his appreciation for the nation's farmers. Trump highlighted the positive impact of his administration's policies, including tax cuts, job creation, and economic growth. He also discussed efforts to reduce regulations and protect the interests of the farming community. The President emphasized the importance of rural infrastructure and broadband internet access for farmers. He signed executive orders to expand broadband access in rural America and support broadband tower facilities. Trump concluded his speech by celebrating the Battle of New Orleans and reiterating his commitment to the American farmer.